# HMPPS Domain Events

Built using [AWS SNS](https://aws.amazon.com/sns/) and [AWS SQS](https://aws.amazon.com/sqs/) in a [fanout configuration](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/sns/latest/dg/sns-sqs-as-subscriber.html), HMPPS domain events is a facility which enables choreographed processes across HMPPS systems.

Events must be published by all domains for all business-level changes as per the ADR - [Domain Events ADR](https://dsdmoj.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/NDSS/pages/2811691200/ADR+-+Publishing+Microservice+Events)

Events must be published as "lightweight", as per the ADR - [Domain Event Schema](https://dsdmoj.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/NDSS/pages/3732570166/ADR+-+Domain+Event+Schema)

